Iranian students are prepared to die for the nuclear programme of their country.
They created a human shield
A few hundred students graduate schools have created a human shield around a nuclear site in Iran.
They want to support this gesture the nuclear programme of their country to face a possible Israeli attack.
Students have to pray at noon in front of the site and then wished the death of the US and Israel.
A few hundred students from the universities of Isfahan have created a human shield around Tuesday nuclear technology centre of Isfahan where uranium is processed.
They have openly expressed that they would defend the program nuclaire their country risking their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) noted in its latest information that Iran has not ceased to strengthen its nuclear weapons.
Reportring in Israel for a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
Students have to pray at noon in front of the site and then wished the death of the US and Israel.
In the event of an attack, whose aim would be to destroy Iran's nuclear program, the targets would not only Isfahan, but also the site of Natanz, where uranium is enriched.
Feeding an obese child: takes no breakfast and takes deli for lunch
More than a third of children aged 9-13 problems of overweight, 9% of écoliersont weight above the average and 5 percent are obese.
As the research shows the current obese children come from families who have an unhealthy lifestyle.
This again shows how important the environment in which human beings and models that surround it.
On the tables of obese children example deli 50% more often than in the families of children in the normal weight.
19% of obese had fries for dinner, according to the survey conducted with outreach "obesity is not an accident"
Families of small big sport is also a habit, which is now the most schoolchildren today - only 15% replied that at least once a week, parents found the time for the movement.
Investigation of 900 children
The survey was conducted during the last school year and participated 900 pupils of primary schools in the Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of "obesity is not a coincidence," sustained action by the General Health Insurance and Unilever.
 From the beginning it is more than 12000 students from sixth to third who have registered for this project.
One of the factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of children who are overweight or obese, is the lack of proper food and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half the children interviewed notes, for example, eat five times a day breakfast event - breakfast, lunch, dinner, which is a basic principles of good nutrition," says one of the results of the investigation.
Without breakfast and lunch deli
Specialists draw attention to the fact that in order to have a healthy development must be a few basic details such as a breakfast family at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of students ' families eat at the same time.
In most families, everyone takes his breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that has been raised is that a tenth of the population does not breakfast.
Breakfast is a good daily diet.
The survey showed that families of obese children consume more often unhealthy fries.
Almost every pupil - not to mention the weight - drink every day sugary drinks (70%).
More than 40% of children questioned the sport regularly but for parents it is half, only 15 per cent.
Prepares you your diet
Another part of the investigation has allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls 13 schools) to prepare its own food from proposed options according to their own taste and their personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far in terms of healthy eating, the ideal."
Among their favorite dishes, there is a lot of cakes, meat and sweets.
"The most alarming is particularly great preference for sweet lemonades," is shown in the results of the investigation.
For lunch it is pasta who took first place just before the white meat.
The children did not want any starch and preference for fish and vegetable meal was very low.
Focus on health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits when they receive the ad hoc information.
"During a control group of participants in the survey who had completed the questionnaire after the meeting" obesity is not a coincidence, "we have attended a definite desire to move towards a healthy diet," indicate the results of the investigation.
The most prominent was for example with regard to the sweet lemonades because children have begun to give preference to water consumption.
Children are most often checked on the questionnaire white meat and fish as the main dish and reduce the sweet dishes and " knedliky (Czech spécialté pellets flour bread or potatoes).
