How prices have changed travel since 1989
Until 1989 there were in Czechoslovakia only 5 travel agencies: Cedok, Sporturist, CKM, Rekrea and Autotourist.
Travel agents at that time offered travel mainly in the country's socialist bloc, because travel to the west were very limited.
The Czech tourists traveled to holidays in East Germany, Soviet Union (Sochi, Crimea and the Black Sea), Bulgaria, Romania (both in the Black Sea) and Hungary (Balaton).
A big exception for the period from 1962 to 1972 when he was allowed to travel in Yugoslavia and the regime began to have an inclination towards the west, and travel to Yugoslavia were very limited for Czech tourists.
The great paradox of the socialist era was that he was not authorized for the citizens of the socialist bloc (also for the Czechs) travel individually even within the framework of the socialist countries.
In cases where the citizen Tchécoslovaque wanted to travel individually for example in Poland and the Soviet Union it needed a letter of invitation or the individual trip was not permitted.
Travel agencies at the time also offered trips to the West, however, it was necessary to queue all night with a sleeping bag or have a "good knowledge" within the travel agency.
And even after that it was not yet won.
The agreement for the currency was the condition for travel to the west was denied to "politically incorrect" people who could not travel at all.
The Czechoslovak currency was not, however, exchangeable and it was not possible to obtain financial resources without the agreement of currencies (Western currency) to travel to the west.
The Czechs spend their vacations more often in the country where there was therefore many houses and cottages that the Czechs are bought and usually lasts until now.
Travel Czechs have since undergone a major revolution since 1989.
Although until 1989 holidays in East Germany and Bulgaria were the maximum, the Czechs have spent the past year abroad 4 million vacation days in countries around the world.
The great paradox of which we have no conscience today is that the most popular is Croatia when it was not possible to go free until 1989 as part of Yugoslavia at the time.
The abolition of visas in the 1990s of the last century in neighbouring countries of the west have caused a huge wave of short-term visits mainly in Austria in Vienna and Germany.
The Czechs could not long travel by air to the west that everyone wanted to see at least a moment.
For example, Paris travel organizations were sleeping Czechs in tents in parks because our income we could not pay the hotel or a pension.
The typical feature of Czechs was at that time to win with its own canned food, sausage, etc... to save.
Another important moment was also the interchangeability of the Czech koruna has enabled our tourists finally after decades of power freely buy Western currency.
Our standard of living as well as the average salary rose causing around 1997 another important moment.
Thanks to a growing demand for travel travel agencies have begun since 1997 to prepare towers with links by charter air through contracts have greatly reduced costs compared to what there was before.
In the late 1990s of the last century the Czechs had links without visas with almost most developed countries around the world to the US later facilitated our trips.
Another interesting moment in the history of tourism post-revolution, when was prepared the first air charter to an exotic country, Thailand, from the Czech Republic.
Since this year as every year, direct air charter take of Czech tourists in distant hot countries; this winter, there will be 12 exotic destinations from the Czech Republic.
It is more than 100000 Czechs who visit the exotic countries every year!
Still an interesting moment in this period that symbolizes our development post-revolution arrived in 2008.
On 17 November 2008, the EU has abolished visas for Czech tourists and allowed our country to stand completely in the group of developed countries.
Also in 2008 the Czechs for the first time in history have spent more than half of their holidays abroad (50.3%) and for the first time in history have spent more than 15000 kronor per person for holidays abroad including annexes loads. Kroner per person.
The General Assembly must find its President but may be terminated by a situation without "solution" pat
Nearly 5mois already Czech football without President and there is a risk that the successor of Ivan Hašek at the head of the Association of Football of the Czech Republic is not yet known after yet another General Assembly to be held Thursday at Nymburk.
However, there is still no agreement on what to vote must proceed.
Without this agreement, it is not possible to begin to vote for one of the three candidates.
Dr. Jindrich Rajchl, Miroslav Pelta and Tomas Paclik are interested in the direction of the Czech football.
Hašek resigned in June and during his departure has called on his colleagues has come together and find a strong personality who will lead the football in the future.
Only during the era after Hašek football came back to differences between the chambers of the Association who cannot agree on a joint candidate.
This was completely shown on September 16 when he had to choose a new president.
Delegates of the General Assembly met unnecessarily in the national House in Prague because the negotiation has been blocked and it has not even been discussed to address how to elect.
There was no agreement on who has the right to vote in the General Assembly only - apparently, the statutory representatives or also those with full powers.
In this single point there was a partial agreement since that moment also with the support of the Office for the state and the law, under which the representation on the basis of full power is not possible.
Differences continue about the rules for the election.
It is all too clear that the executive committee, which in its planned or extraordinary negotiation has contributed nothing to the situation
Opinions on the voting possibilitě have changed several times, but the key point is always the same.
The question is: how to proceed in the third round to avoid falling into the pat.
"The bone of contention is the following fact: either proceed according to the statutes or find another model," was one of three vice-presidents of the Football Association of the Czech Republic Dusan Svoboda representing professional football within the association.
According to the rules of the planned model won the third round of candidates who have received the most votes in percentage terms in the chamber for which he is a candidate.
Moravia is prepared according to what is said to withdraw so that the candidate who has received the highest percentage of votes of the two chambers.
And the Czech Republic is studying the condition that the winner should have at least two-thirds of the percentages of votes.
"Only this would then lose the idea of two previous rounds and it would completely reject the bicameral concept," admits Svoboda who understands the objections of the Moravian party and that it would be best not to change the rules and vote according to existing statutes.
It is surprising that Tomas Paclik also agree even if he believes that the electoral rules established by statute advantage Pelta among all the candidates.
"I hope that the vote under the statutes of the association."
"There is still no insane ideas dreamt up by a representative as during the past general assemblies," said the owner of Victoria Plzen, who is a candidate for the first time and in its submissions has defined mainly against Pelta.
Pelta remains optimistic.
According to Nymburk there will be a new President and believes that the candidates will cooperate in the future together and constructively.
"The possible qualification today in European Championships should calm everybody."
"Football on a wave of happiness and one more more joy for cooperation," added the officer Jablonec which of the three has the greatest experience of leadership of both professional football and regionally.
Rajchl is more pessimistic.
"I believe in this agreement, but unfortunately the situation is very tense."
"This is not a problem between the Czechs and the Moravians, but there are trends in wanting to change the design regulations."
"This can lead to a new blockage at the General Assembly."
"I hope that the sound reason will win," said Rajchl.
There is not much time for a joint agreement to all parties.
Some réuunions should be held directly in Montenegro but who can say whether the entire direction of football will be full for the match.
The specially chartered flight in which to travel up to Podgorice among other Vice-Presidents Dalibor Kucera and Rajchl, has not taken off for technical reasons and was looking for an alternative to take part of the executive committee on the ground of reprisals.
At the end it is the ministerial meeting, which could be held on Wednesday, which should be decisive.
The Education Minister of Youth and Sport Dobes Joseph would be very happy to receive the parties torn within the sports association, the largest in the country and bring them to an agreement.
In the game there is a lot: a state appropriation, the credibility of football and the General Assembly of the Czech Sports Union should determine the direction of the Czech sport after the financial problems of Sazka.
