For the same reason, he refused to let Breivik, who has brought with him a speech on paper, talk to the parents of the victims at the end of the hearing.
The judge Nesheim has also asked the police to keep Breivik in custody for 12 weeks, he was forbidden to speak to the media for four weeks and has warned that the authorities would monitor very closely all visits and correspondence for eight weeks.
Some 30 relatives of survivors and victims were present at the hearing.
Some came in the hope of watching Breivik in the eye, others to make sure that it would be placed behind bars.
All attended the hearing in order to see the end of the trial.
