He has a vision of how things can be and should be.
He then explained the dishes away.
Here is a quick summary of seven remarkable sequence of Lost Interview:
On the way he has learned to run a business:
" During all these years, I have always asked: ' Why are you doing things? " And the answers are always the same: ' Oh, simply because we need to make them. "
Nobody knows why nobody is thinking in depth in a company.
That is what I discovered.
Steve Jobs continues giving details on its efforts to simplify accounting at Apple.
Puzzled as to how the costs were registered - often begins with a "standard cost" evaluated for nose, then adjusted with a "variation" - he has developed an automated plant that would guarantee a precise calculation of costs.
The opportunity to play a round on the Pope:
Steve Jobs tells the story of the "blue box" that he has created with Steve Wozniak - a device that was used to hack into telephone networks and call free long-distance.
