We did not know much, but we have been able to invent a small thing capable of controlling great things; it was an incredible lesson, and I do not believe that Apple would one day have existed without it.
Steve Jobs continues by telling a wonderful tour that he and Wozniak have developed: he phoned the Vatican with the blue in the middle of the night by impersonating Henry Kissinger and asked to speak to the Pope.
