The low temperatures of February, cause losses trillion for the agricultural sector, have limited the ability of the state's economy for growth, have caused a contraction of economic activity in general by 3.6 percent in the first half of the year, mainly justified by the historic decline of 31.16 percent in agriculture, which has affected the dynamism of other economic sectors.
According to the report of assignments by the frosts produced by the Mexican Council Development Rurale Sustainable, there has been damage to 582 million 835 hectares, including a 78.03 per cent have suffered the total damage and the rest of 21.07 per cent have suffered partial damage, the main crops affected were the vegetables, corn and chickpeas.
The decline in economic activity generated until November, a steady rise in unemployment in the state, according to the National Institute of Statistics and Geography the unemployment rate in the state during the first three quarters of the year there has been a rapid increase, because during the January to March 55 thousand 053 sinaloens were unemployed, with a rate of 4.53 percent of the Économique Labour, in the second quarter, the rate is now 5.28 percent and the July to September the average continued to raise up to 6.19 percent, a rate that represents more than 74 miles sinaloens unemployed, an increase compared to the first half of 18000 969 people.
Less liquidity
Unemployment in Sinaloa during the year is multifactorial, according to the economist Gerardo Lopez Cervantes, director of the Faculty of Sciences Economic and Social of UAS, rising unemployment can be explained indirectly depending on the actions carried out by public policy.
"That is an increase in unemployment, which is due to various factors, among which the loss of liquidity in the market due to a restriction of resources by legislation approved in Congress to combat money laundering, because for people who earn dollars an unlawful manner is not easy work for the win, they invest them and use them in something," he says.
Detained migration
López Cervantes said that rising unemployment is also due to a demographic factor.
"The number of people who leave the state to go to work abroad, the United States has been limited, first because of the difficulty of entry and secondly because entering they already have a lot of difficulties in finding work, these people remain here and ask sources of work, which means that unemployment rise," said.
Lack of seriousness
The analysis of the labour market sinaloen worsens in considering the high level of lack of seriousness that predominates among the working conditions, according to the INEGI, 60.38 percent of the population involved in this state is working without pay as a worker in any social insurance institution.
Apart from unemployment and the lack of seriousness, another reason to lag in the state are low wages, the entity has the lowest wages in the country, according to the records of the Mexican Institute of Social Insurance and the Secretariat of Labour and Social Forecasting.
The average monthly income of workers sinaloens was until September 5 thousand 352 pesos, well below the national average, which stands at 7 thousand 375 pesos.
Contraction of FDI
The decline in economic activity and rising unemployment in 2011 we recorded the greatest reduction in Foreign Direct Investment of the last 10 years, according to the Secretariat of Economics from January to June the FDI state has reached 630 thousand 697 million, representing a decrease of 87.74 percent compared to 5 million 143 thousand 312 million recorded in the same period the previous year.
In turn, the Secretariat of Economic Development of the State Government accrued a total investment of 17.280 trillion pesos per year, mainly recorded by companies of the tertiary sector.
Debt
Given the scenario of economic contraction, the State Government has requested in July at the congress public approval of a $3 trillion pesos, for investment in infrastructure projects in the 18 municipes, with the aim to reactivate the economy, congressional approval of the State was 2.600 trillion pesos and until November there was no benefit of debt in any sector of the economy of the state.
Reactions
The representatives of the business sector, the first year of Government Mario López Valdés demonstrates a lack of management capacity of the Government.
Miguel Loredo López, president of the National Industry Chamber of Transformation, said that in 2011 there has not been a harmonization of the wishes of the various sectors, including the State Government.
"The performance of the economy of Sinaloa during this year has been really very poor, we must work hard to recover the ground we have lost this year in 2012 we must double our effort, it was necessary to bring the effort and especially good already synchronized march of this new Government team, let us hope that next year will be much better," he said.
Slow economic
Loredo López said that events such as the frozen at the beginning of the year have been the state's economy and have restricted its performance and growth.
"The bottom fluxe economic product of several events, among which the jellies, one of the main effects has been a slow economy that is fast enough to generate an economic dynamism that allows an acceptable level e flows in the trials, products and services and therefore, at the end of the year we are closing much below the expectations that we had," he says.
Redefining the vocation
For Teodoro Salazar Uriarte, president of Management Confederation of Mexican Sinaloa stated that it wants to harness the state towards productive activities more dynamism.
"In general terms we have observed that we worked, we believe it is necessary to develop a long-term programme that redefined the vocation and the economic direction of the state, because it is important that detonates the full potential of material and human resources of Sinaloa," he says.
Much to do
The chairman of the Coparmex stressed the importance of establishing a future vision that channels better efforts by the Government.
"In general terms, I would say that the Government has made efforts to give good results in various fields, in terms of economic development, there are some advances, but it is important to develop a programma long-term," he said.
He pointed out that the current administration has shown advances in the management of public policy.
"There are elements that allow us to say that the Government is more inclusive, what I can say is that we have worked hard and the Government is aware of the fact that there is still much to do," he says.
