A person Novolato resident was sentenced to five years in prison and a fine of 100 days for possession of eight kilograms of marijuana.
The Attorney General of the Republic has informed that the small convicted trafficker is Omar Alexis Valenzuela Sandoval, for crimes against health, in its variant of possession of marijuana for sale.
According to the AP/NISs file/CLN/687/2010/M-I, Valenzuela Sandoval was arrested by agents of the Mexican Army on 7 June 2010 during a surveillance operation in the street Cipriano Valdez, before the number 80 El Castillo, Navolato.
The small trafficker was riding in a pickup truck pick-up white, in which he was carrying a bag of black in the baggage of the vehicle and the place of the copilot, a small backpack, where the military have found eight kilograms and 23 grams of marijuana.
For this reason, the confiscated items were available to the Second District Judge and the condemned is still in the Centre Delivery Consequences of Legal Crimes.
Debts to contributions to books
The works of social coherence in programs such as Hábitat, Rescate of Spaces Públicos and para 3x1 migrants may not be finished when registering serious delays due to a lack of economic resources, Miguel Ángel López reported Miranda.
The director of municipal Social Development said that although so far the construction programmes have progressed, they find themselves in a situation of risk, because the State Government is acquitted its obligations to provide contributions that exceed 11 million pesos in the three programs.
He noted that in total investment of these three programs is approximately 50 million pesos, which the state must provide 25 percent and so far only the Federation and the Municipe have provided resources for books, therefore there is the possibility of a delay in their final stages.
"They must provide a contribution of $12 million, and despite the fact that the year will soon conclude they have given us nothing, although since July they should give us a party," he says, "and we, to register no delays, we began the books and we have come a long way, but we need the money."
He mentioned that last year, during the administration of Jesús Aguilar Padilla, the state had not paid the corresponding contributions, therefore, at the beginning of the administration Municipe had to request a credit to cover the 7 million that the administration of the state had not provided on this occasion.
"We had already suffered in the previous six-year period because the state did not have the economic capacity to participate and programs continue to function and this year, to be able to have access to these programs, we duu get the resources to cover what the state had not paid," détailla.
Despite the fact that there is a commitment on the part of the authorities of the state to provide these resources, he said they had asked the Secretary of Administration and Finance, Armando Villarreal, to activate the management for the corresponding percentages arrive as soon as possible.
"They must provide almost 12 million, and despite the fact that the year will soon end, they have given us nothing."
The Court validates "analog cut" in Mexico in 2015
The substitution of analogue reported by the finger is one of the most important changes that the world has suffered the last few years
The Supreme Court of Justice's (SCJN) dismissed the constitutional controversy that the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies have made against the presidential decree that advance the so-called "analog" cut from 2021 to 2015, as the eight votes needed to invalidate have not been met.
A minority of four ministers, including the President of the Court, Juan Silva Meza, considered that President Felipe Calderón has not exceeded his authority when he issued the decree detailing the actions to follow to make the transition to the digital terrestrial television.
With this result, the constitutional controversy promoted by the Senate of the Republic, was dismissed for failing to reach a qualified majority of eight votes for the Court to rule on the constitutionality or non-constitutionality of the decree, and this continues to be in force.
The draft sentence, developed by Minister Olga Sánchez Cordero, suggested the statement of the decree as non-constitutional, due to the fact that the regulation of television and radio is an award reserved by law to the Federal Telecommunications Commission (Cofetel), in contravention of the principles of subordination and reserve law.
In favour of the project have voted only Zaldívar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and even Sánchez Cordero.
With this argument, the Senate as the Chamber of Deputies have promoted two constitutional controversy to challenge the decree and complaints, Minister Sánchez Cordero has suspended the implementation of the decree and all actions planned for the digital transition.
The plenary meeting of ministers has resolved to dismiss the complaint made by the Chamber of Deputies, without discussing the project with the Minister Sánchez Cordero is also responsible.
In his speech, the President said that he did not agree with the arguments of the project, in the sense that the Federal Executive cannot structure through general standards that the public administration is preparing.
"I believe that if it did it would affect the autonomy of the regulatory body," and he recalled that the planning of public policies in strategic areas such as the telecommunications sector is the responsibility of the federal executive, which has constitutional mandate for the leadership of the state.
The substitution of analogue reported by digital reported is one of the most important changes that the world has suffered the last few years and this translates into better use of the radio spectrum, better signal quality and more channels.
Postpone the change, argued it would postpone the benefits of the digitisation involves a decision of public interest which has not only a technical dimension, "because it also includes economic, social and political issues of national security."
These issues, stressed, "require the operation of an entire system, in accordance with the principle of economic direction of the state, includes a group of powers that the Constitution gives the power of the executive of the state."
He recalled that a large number of countries across the world have already finished the digital transition, and they have done through the executive, despite the fact that they had the highly specialized technical bodies.
We cannot conclude that the executive, emitting the contested decree has invaded a form the competences of Congress, because it provides in the sphere of administrative compliance with laws issued by the Legislative, he says.
An analysis of the possibility of a "vote by vote count" Michoacán
According to the data highlighted by PER, the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 6 thousand 74 minutes total.
The possibility of "vote by vote count" is a reality in relation to the electoral trial this year in Michoacán, where according to the data highlighted by the Results Program Électoraux Preparations (PER) the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor is only 27 percent, even without counting the votes corresponding to 879 6 thousand 74 minutes total.
In this sense, the president of the General Council of the Electoral Institute of Michoacán (EMP), Maria de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, the past November 9, the electoral body has approved a series of guidelines to harmonize the local standards at the federal reform.
You will recall that Michoacán has not approved or its Constitution Policy nor his Electoral Code of State or Justice Act Electoral, at the same time as the state Congress approved the reforms shortly before that end the legal deadline for this electoral trial can enter into force and the governor Leonel Godoy Rangel failed its publication deadlines under the Law of the Official Journal of the state, with the argument that he had some objections.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice's (SCJN) has solved the constitutional controversy promoted by the local Legislative Power and described as "invalid and illegal" the vote of the agent for the constitutional reforms, because it does not have the right to "punish or challenge."
Interviewed on the possibility of "vote by vote," Maria de los Ángeles Llanderal said that thanks to the approval of the guidelines by the General Council of IEM it will be possible to achieve the partial and total counts votes by the local electoral body.
Thus, the partial count of votes, one or more electoral packages, it may be that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no record of voting and counting in the case of the ballot box is not the president; or there are obvious errors or alterations in minutes.
In addition, the total number of votes received in all polls of the election can be achieved when there is an indication that the difference between the presumed winner of the election and has secured the second place in the poll is equal to or below a percentage point, provided that at the beginning of the session is a petition express the representative of the party and/or coalition presented the second candidates reported.
The total amount of voting can also be achieved if at the end of the count, it follows that the difference between the supposed winner and second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is a specific petition by the representative of the political party whose candidate came second, in which case we will exclude the electoral packets that have been subject of the partial count.
It should be noted that this is the situation of the election of Morelia, where according to the PER, the difference between the first and second place is only 0.16 percent, even without counting the votes of 129 of 923 minutes total.
