His ashes will be prevalent in the Zapalinamé Sierra, confirms the family.
The remains of the pilot Felipe Bacio Cortés arrive in Saltillo, his hometown, this Sunday to the night, and on Monday, people will present their tributes and there will be a being of requiem.
According to his family, the final determination of the lieutenant colonel was that his ashes are prevalent in the Zapalinamé Sierra.
After receiving the tributes alongside other people died in the accident, the family of Bacio Cortés returned to the capital of Coahuila on board an aircraft Forces Aériennes Mexicans, the closest attended the ceremony at Campo Marte.
