" He wanted to return to Saltillo and that his ashes are prevalent in the Zapalinamé Sierra, he has always said that " his family and friends, " Sandra contacted Bacio Cortés, sister of the pilot.
The lieutenant colonel had made all his dreams, it was in the fullness of his life, "he was successful, he was a father and son, extraordinary, a loving brother and much treated his family."
Felipe Bacio Cortés has abandoned the very young city of Saltillo to register at the College of the Air Zapopán, Jalisco.
Some couldn't believe it, because they said it was even difficult truck; but he has always followed his dream of becoming a pilot.
Her nephew Jorge Alberto Dávila Bacio remembers that it was a very good person, "when he was in Saltillo family wanted to welcome, as was the opportunity in which Martha Sahagún in Saltillo."
The young man even remembers that when he was 7 years old he has travelled to Zapopán for the graduation of its parent, that he knows that his uncle is dies in doing what he loved most in life: fly an aircraft.
His final farewell
