Fujimori again hospitalized for medical tests
Former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized Tuesday in a public hospital to be evaluated for the loss of muscle strength in magpies, informed his family doctor.
Fujimori, 72, who is serving a sentence of 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his government (1990-2000) is suffering from various ailments, including cancer language for which he was operated on four times and is under control.
Congressman Alejandro Aguinaga, his personal physician, said Canal N television that Fujimori will be evaluated for three days in the National Institute of Néoplasiques diseases to determine the reason for the pain and loss of strength in his legs.
Aguinaga commented that in his opinion Fujimori would be a candidate for the benefit of the penalty for humanitarian reasons, without doubt, he said that it wants because it feels innocent.
He underwent cancer four times language, it has a weight loss of weight 18 kilograms, and other diseases, such as a severe erosive gastritis, a cyst, pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and traffic problems in the feet, said the doctor.
Fujimori is serving life imprisonment since September 2007 in the National Directorate of Operations Special Police.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the death of 25 people because of a squadron of annihilation of the army, which has operated clandestinely during the early years of his government.
Mujica trip to Mexico to strengthen political ties
A formal procession, to head the Uruguayan President José Mujica, and various ministers and bosses, will initiate a visit Tuesday to Mexico to expand trade between the two nations and address political issues in the region.
Mujica will meet next Wednesday with his Mexican counterpart, Felipe Calderón, the highest point of a long agenda of meetings with political authorities, trade, and a meeting with the community of Uruguayan residents in Mexico, according to the agenda distributed by the Uruguayan Presidency.
The meeting between the two presidents in the city of Guadalajara, will be "conducive to the exchange of information in the political affairs between the two nations," according to information published by the Presidency of the South American country on its web page.
According to local media, Mujica seeks to convince Calderón to support Uruguay in the incident with France, which took place when the agent of France, Nicolas Sarkozy, has included the South American country on the list of tax havens in the G20 meeting in the French city of Cannes.
In his speech, Sarkozy has threatened to exclude from the international community, the countries that continue to be tax havens, a statement that led to the rejection of Uruguay and the call for consultations its ambassador to the European country.
Mexico has chaired since November the G20, a group of emerging and developed countries in the world, and has in place with the South American country since January this year, an agreement to exchange tax information to avoid double taxation.
The Uruguayan government has tried in recent years to send the realization of tax exchange agreements to emerge from the "gri list" of the Organization for Cooperation and Economic Development (OECD), integrated by countries that do not implement all international standards for cooperation in tax matters.
Commercially, Mexico and Uruguay have been in force since 2004 a Treaty Free Trade (TLC), which has increased the exchange of goods between the two nations.
The moustachu plumber goes to three dimensions with ' Super Mario 3D Land "
Super Mario has fought, indefatigable, for 25 years to save the Princess Peach from the clutches of Bowser villain, but he never did in three dimensions: in "Super Mario 3D Land" will contend for the love of the young in stereoscopic technology.
The title, which arrives this month to stores across the world, has been designed from the beginning to exploit the characteristics of the portable console Nintendo 3DS, which can play in three dimensions without the use of glasses.
"Mario is the man who must say must function as the stéréoscopie without glasses," said the head of press for Nintendo in Spain, Omar Alvarez, during the presentation of the video game in Madrid.
Alvarez said that "Super Mario 3D Land" is "the first video game Nintendo originally designed for this medium," because so far success as "Star Fox 64 3D" or "Zelda: Ocarine of time 3D" was adaptations of existing titles.
The spokesman for Nintendo argued that, despite being in 3D, "Super Mario 3D Land" is a "accessible" video game that allows a fast and fluid.
Alvarez said that "Super Mario 3D Land" contains two games in one: the first part is "simple" to hang the least adept users.
Once overcome, experts will be able to make a "second round" levels of play, this time are more difficult.
In addition, users can choose between an "aggressive" or one that affects only the depth of the action, but it would be necessary to play in three dimensions to overcome the various challenges and "succumbing to optical illusions."
This incursion of Super Mario in all three dimensions also requires the return of a mobile console, a fact that was happening more since 2005.
In these video games, Nintendo is a nod to the followers of the saga and repeat the formula for success of previous games, which lies in the fact that the moustachu plumber must travel undermined platforms perils to liberate the Princess Peach.
Even though I player found in new movements, environments, costumes and enemies and also in the case of Luigi "feasible."
Colom gives its blessing to the extradition of Portillo in the United States
President Alvaro Colom announced last Tuesday that he had ordered the extradition of the former governor Alfonso Portillo to meet the United States for conspiracy to launder 70 million US dollars.
Thus ends the trial for Guatemala to respond to the request of the northern countries calling for Portillo to try.
In a press conference, Colom said that its decision obeys the independence of the judiciary and executive taking into account the fact that a trial court had already ordered his extradition.
He said that during his term, "he had not helped" in any judicial resolution and he had given way to all extraditions that he had known.
Apart from Portillo, Sergio Ruano Marroquín will also be extradited for murder and serious injury, and Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes will be extradited for drug trafficking.
What Colom pointed assumes executive after exhausting all judicial and constitutional bodies to try the former agent of the 2004-2004 period.
According to the resolutions of the Fifth Criminal Court and the Court of Constitutionality (CC), Portillo should be extradited after resolving his legal situation in Guatemala and having secured his human rights.
Portillo was absolute for misappropriation of funds was the Ministry of Defence million when he was president, who was the trial that preceded the extradition, but the Public Ministry has appealed and has revived the case.
